Judges are asked to protect themselves from the presidents.
The Presidential Human Rights Council (HRC) on behalf of Vladimir Putin has developed proposals to strengthen the independence of the judicial branch of power.
The HRC proposes to limit the powers of the presidents of the courts and introduce their elective powers.
For the courts of appeal and cassation bodies, the HRC wants to introduce special districts that will not be tied to the administrative and territorial division in the Russian Federation.
His proposals within the framework of the presidential commission should also be presented by the Supreme Court.
The HRC has completed the development of proposals that will strengthen the independence of Russian justice.
This work was carried out by the HRC on behalf of Vladimir Putin on January 3, 2017, which the President gave after meeting with members of the Council.
At the meeting with the members of the Council on 8 December 2016, individual cases of judicial arbitrariness, as well as problems of public control in the places of detention of citizens were discussed (see "E" of 9 December).
The results of the work of the HRC were 25 proposals, which deal with issues of ensuring the independence of judges and the identification of judicial errors, as well as the financing of courts and legal education.
One of the ideas of the Kremlin human rights defenders is to limit the powers of the presidents of the courts to increase the independence of other judges.
If the candidate for the position of judge has successfully passed the competition and has received the support of the judiciary, then the President of the Court, in the opinion of the HRH, must present him for appointment, without having the right to refuse, as the law now allows.
It is also proposed to deprive the President of the right to distribute cases to the judges.
To do this, experts allow, can specially written computer program.
Also, the HRC believes that the chairman is not entitled "to determine the results of the qualification certificate of the judge, to initiate his involvement in disciplinary responsibility, to make decisions on the establishment of additional material payments".
At the same time, the Presidential Council considers it necessary to go to the "election of the chairmen of the courts by the judges themselves" and "give them powers for a relatively short period with mandatory rotation".
Now all the presidents of the courts (from the republican to the district) are appointed for six years by the president on the proposal of the president of the Supreme Court of the Russian Federation.
In order to protect judges from pressure from regional administrations, the HRH proposes to reorganize appeal and cassation in the courts of general jurisdiction.
Now their structure is tied to the administrative-territorial division in the Russian Federation.
It is necessary to ensure the organization of individual courts of appeal and cassation bodies not at the level of regional judicial bodies in the subjects of the Russian Federation, but in judicial districts.
Experts are based on the practice of arbitral tribunals.
There are “judicial districts” that do not coincide with the administrative division in the Russian Federation, but guarantee greater independence from regional officials who find it difficult to use the “phone law”.
World Judges HRC proposes to strengthen the people's deputies to consider with their participation some "categories of civil and administrative cases".
For example, the deprivation of parental rights, the restoration of work, the protection of honor and dignity, the deprivation of driving rights, etc.
"These are just our proposals," explained the member of the Constitutional Court, the judge of the Constitutional Court in the resignation of Tamara Morshchakov.
She also recalled that the President’s injunction was not only for the HRC, but also for the Supreme Court, which had not yet disclosed its proposals.
The time for carrying out the assignment to the Armed Forces (among the co-executors - the Prosecutor General's Office and the Commissioner for Human Rights in the Russian Federation) still exists.
To report to Vladimir Putin about how effectively the independence of justice is ensured in Russia, the President of the Armed Forces Vyacheslav Lebedev should before September 1.
