It was not possible to get an operational comment from CENKI on Thursday, and Mr. Okhlopkov himself was not available for comments.
However, the information "U" has been officially confirmed in the GNCC.
He decided to move to the position of Director of Production Coordination, - stated at the enterprise. - Andrey Okhlopkov has fully fulfilled the task assigned to him to ensure the launch minimum for the first launch at the cosmodrome of the East.
Mr. Okhlopkov moved to work at the CENKI in 2013, having served behind the shoulders in space troops, in particular in Baikonur, and in Plesetsk - at the "northern" cosmodrome he held the position of first deputy commander in the rank of colonel.
In 2009, Andrey Okhlopkov became a criminal case figure.
The investigation accused him of bribery: allegedly, from his submission, regional merchants received government orders for recoils, but did not fulfill their obligations to clean the separate parts of the carrier missiles in the Arkhangelsk region and the Republic of Komi.
In 2012, the jury found him innocent.
The duties on technological development assigned to him at CENKI were extended to various projects, but the main of them was the construction of a cosmodrome in the Far East.
Oleg Ostapenko, then head of the Federal Space Agency, in an interview with E, said directly that the situation in the East "was critical as early as October 2013."
The fact is that a strategic mistake was made in the planning: the completion of the construction and the first launch of the Soyuz-2.1 carrier rocket were planned for the same time - the end of 2015.
In order to carry out the launch before the end of the year, it was decided to complete the construction half a year earlier and the deadlines were postponed from December to July 2015.
To speed up the process, the trick had to go: CENKI specialists began to carry out parallel installation of technological equipment on unfinished facilities.
The main supporter of this idea was Andrei Okhlopkov.
Despite the existing risks and the transfer that took place (instead of December 2015 the Soyuz only flew on April 28, 2016), this idea proved to be true, says the source of the "U" at the cosmodrome: "Otherwise we would not have made a single launch from the East, but would have been engaged in construction".
Deputy Prime Minister Dmitry Rogozin, who oversees the creation of the cosmodrome, jokingly called Andrey Okhlopkov his "cosmic Susanin", but it was he who almost always asked for information about the construction.
Mr. Okhlopkov remembered and straight: for example, in an interview with "U" he proposed to deprive the Federal Agency for Special Construction (Spetstroj) of the status of the only performer in the East and directly work with subcontractors: "Why should we lay all the eggs in one basket?"
This idea was supported by the government.
Since 2017, CENKI has assumed the responsibilities of a general contractor to complete construction and installation work on the start-up and technical complex by the planned launches in the fourth quarter.
According to "U", the reason for the transition of Mr. Okhlopkov to the new place of work were disagreements with the management of CENKI regarding the ways of completing the construction of structures and complexes of the cosmodrome, as well as the methods of work with subcontracting organizations.
“It was decided that this would be better for everyone,” says one of the top managers involved in the construction of the East.
An employee of the government apparatus, in turn, calls the decision strange: "He was one of the best specialists, it will not be easy to find an equivalent replacement for him."
According to "U", this will not be necessary: the post of technical director of the cosmodrome will be abolished, and its functions will be distributed among the units of CENKI.
