As the organizers promise, the platform will become a territory of improvisation and a field for demonstrating new creative opportunities.
"The guests of the festival will be able to immerse themselves in the world of experimental media technologies and learn how innovations in science become a new tool for interaction with art," Elena Zelentsova, vice-president of the Skolkovo Foundation, said in a statement.
Among the participants of Skolkovo Jazz Science 2017 many stars, including the Moscow Jazz Orchestra of Igor Butman, who will present a joint program with vocalist Yaroslava Simonova.
Jazz and science are related concepts, and they did not coincidentally come together, - explained the popular artist "Izvestia".
The experiment and improvisation of jazz music is valued as much as scientists.
One of the main events of the festival will be the performance of Azekel, a British of Nigerian origin, known for both his own creativity and his collaboration with the legendary Massive Attack and Gorillaz.
Jazz fans are looking forward to the performance of the first in Russia five-time Grammy Award nominee, pianist Christian Sands (USA) with his trio.
In the new capacity will try one of the best academic chamber orchestras "Music Viva" under the direction of Alexander Rudin and with the participation of pianist Yuri Favorin.
The fusion of jazz, ethnic and electronic music, as well as academic traditions, will be demonstrated by the Marimba Plus ensemble and its leader, composer and marimba performer Lea Slepner.
One of the most unusual festival performances promises to be the set of the award winner Sergei Kurehin Anton Maskeliadze.
The artist-experimenter manages music and video with gestures - this is how the technology of leap motion works.
In total, eight musical groups will perform on two stages of the festival.
In addition, the program includes open discussions, interactive areas and art objects, united by the idea of merging music and science.
Guests will be able to take part in experiments, visit the scientific buffet and observe the creation of frosted or buoyant sands from starch and water.
In the special zone of vinyl, it will be possible to buy records of actual jazz performers and representatives of other musical directions, and at the book fair - publications on various topics, including musical, scientific-popular and biomedical literature.
