Electricity is cheap for both the residents and the producers of Buryatia
The decades-long efforts of the Soviet and post-Soviet authorities of the Republic of Buryatia (Eastern Siberia) to establish fair tariffs for electricity consumers are beginning to bear fruit.
From 1 September, the cost of low-voltage electricity for industrial recipients will be reduced by 25%.
The Federal Antimonopoly Service of the country in accordance with the Resolution of the Government of the Russian Federation "On Amendments to the Rules of the Wholesale Market of Electricity and Power and to the Combined Forecast Balance of Production and Supply of Electricity (Power) in the framework of the Unified Energy System of the Russian Federation on the prices" (No 17.07.2017).
As a result, the cost of electricity for Buryat commodity producers is reduced by a quarter, which will significantly facilitate the lives of small and medium-sized enterprises and individual entrepreneurs.
For many decades, the leaders of the republic have bypassed the thresholds of Moscow's cabinets in vain attempts to level the region in tariffs with the neighboring Irkutsk region with a cascade of hydroelectric power plants on the Angara, flowing from Baikal, the main watershed for which is Buryatia.
It was only this year that the movement began.
In March, electricity tariffs for the population of the Republic were reduced from 4.24 rubles/kWh to 3.93 rubles/kWh, or 7.3%.
With the inclusion of Buryatia on the decision of the federal government in the List of territories of price zones of the wholesale market, for which the features of the functioning of wholesale and retail markets are established, a number of industrial consumers have emerged.
According to analysts, this is only the beginning, as the population of the Irkutsk region pays for kilowatt/hour 1.01 rubles.
But no one dares to name at least the approximate date of new tariff moves towards a decline for Buryatia.
